## Early life

Groeschel was born in 1967 in Oklahoma City, Oklahoma. He grew up in a Christian home and was raised in the Church of Christ. He attended Oklahoma Christian University, where he received a Bachelor of Arts in Bible and Theology. He then attended Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary, where he received a Master of Divinity.

## Career

Groeschel is the founding and senior pastor of LifeChurch.tv, a multi-site church in the United States. He is also the author of several books, including "The Christian Atheist" and "It."

## Personal life

Groeschel is married to Amy, and they have three children.

Wangari Maathai was a Kenyan environmentalist and politician. She was the first African woman to receive the Nobel Peace Prize.

## Early life

Wangari Maathai was born in 1940 in Nyeri, Kenya. She was the daughter of a farmer and a schoolteacher. She was the second of eight children.

## Education

Maathai attended St. Anthony Girls High School in Nyeri, Kenya. She then attended Mount St. Scholastica College in Atchison, Kansas, United States. She then received a Ph.D. in Biology from the University of Nairobi in 1971.

input: Write a short biography of Daniel Kahneman.
output:
Daniel Kahneman was born in Tel Aviv, Israel, in 1934. He received his B.A. from the Hebrew University of Jerusalem in 1954 and his Ph.D. from the University of California, Berkeley, in 1958. He taught at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem from 1958 to 1968, and at the University of British Columbia from 1968 to 1978. He was a professor of psychology and public affairs at Princeton University from 1978 to 2000. He is currently a professor of psychology and public affairs at the Woodrow Wilson School of Public and International Affairs at Princeton University.

Kahneman is the author of the book Thinking, Fast and Slow, which won the 2011 Nobel Prize in Economics.

input: Write a short biography of Tilda Swinton.
output:
Tilda Swinton

Tilda Swinton

BiographieAutres informations

## Biographie

Tilda Swinton est née le 5 novembre 1960 à Londres. Elle est la fille de Roger Swinton, un ancien pilote de chasse, et de Judith Balfour, une écrivaine. Elle a un frère, Sandy, et une sœur, Katherine.

Elle a étudié à la West Heath School, à Londres, puis à la University of Cambridge, où elle a obtenu un diplôme en littérature anglaise.

Elle a commencé sa carrière d'actrice en 1984, dans le film Orlando, de Sally Potter.

Elle a été mariée à John Byrne, un peintre, de 1989 à 1997.

Elle a deux enfants, Xavier et Honor, nés en 1997 et 2006, respectivement de son mariage avec l'acteur John Byrne et de son mariage avec l'acteur et réalisateur, Sandro Kopp.

input: Write a short biography of Olivia Colman.

OLIVIA COLMAN

BY

MARY H. WILSON

AUTHOR OF "THE LIFE OF MRS. SIDNEY SMITH," "THE LIFE OF MRS. GEORGE SAND," ETC.

LONDON: TINSLEY BROTHERS, 18, CATHERINE STREET, STRAND.

1875.

[_The Right of Translation is reserved._]

PREFACE.

The following pages are intended to give a short sketch of the life of Olivia Colman, the actress, and to show how she has risen from the position of a poor girl, who, at the age of fourteen, was earning her living by teaching, to that of a lady of fortune, who has been able to indulge her taste for the fine arts, and to surround herself with all the luxuries of life.

The writer has endeavoured to give a faithful account of the life of this actress, and has endeavoured to do so in a manner which will be interesting to the general reader.

M. H. W.

input: Write a short biography of Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie.
output:
CHIMAMANDA NGOZI ADICHIE

_A Short Biography_

Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie was born in Nigeria in 1977. She is the author of the novels _Purple Hibiscus_ (2003), which won the Commonwealth Writers' Prize and the Hurston/Wright Legacy Award; _Half of a Yellow Sun_ (2006), which won the Orange Prize for Fiction; and _Americanah_ (2013), which won the National Book Critics Circle Award and was a finalist for the National Book Award. Her short story collection, _The Thing Around Your Neck_ (2009), was a National Book Critics Circle Award finalist. Her work has received numerous awards and has been translated into thirty languages. She is a recipient of a MacArthur Fellowship, has been named one of the world's 100 most influential people by _Time_ magazine, and is a member of the American Academy of Arts and Letters. She lives in the United States.
